WRITING.TEXT: Ingredients: Green Lentils: 1 cup Oats : 1/2 cup Walnuts: 1/3 cup Raisins: 1/4 cup Olive oil : 1/2 Tbs Bread Crumbs : 3 Tbs Flax seeds : 3 Tbs Onion: 1 small Bell Pepper :1 medium carrot: 1 Medium garlic : 3 cloves salt : to taste Pepper : 1 tsp chili flakes : 1 tsp rosemary : 1/2 Tsp oregano : 1/2 Tsp For glaze Ketchup : 2 Tbs Coconut sugar : 1 Tbs Apple cider vinegar :1 Tbs soya sauce : 1 Tbs Instructions: Preheat oven at 180C. Cook lentil according to instructions on packet. Prepare vegetables. In a pan heat oil add garlic and onion, Fry until color turns to golden brown. Add chopped bell peppers and grated carrots. Stir fry until veggies softened. Now add Raisins, breadcrumbs, oats , Walnuts and seasoning. Continue cooking for 5 minutes. Blend cooked lentils. Prepare flax seed egg by adding water into grounded flax seeds. Add blended lentils and flax seed egg into cooked vegetable mixture. Mix well and set this mixture gently and firmly into loaf pan. Bake for 35 o 40 Minutes on 180C or until its corner turns brown. once baked transfer from loaf pan to board and coat with glaze. Once cool down, carefully slice the loaf into slabs. WRITING.TEXT: Vegan Lentil Loaf For video recipe click here [Vegan Lentil Loaf](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E1qhEBdy1vw) Ingredients: Green Lentils: 1 cup Oats : 1/2 cup Walnuts: 1/3 cup Raisins: 1/4 cup Olive oil : 1/2 Tbs Bread Crumbs : 3 Tbs Flax seeds : 3 Tbs Onion: 1 small Bell Pepper :1 medium Carrot: 1 Medium Garlic : 3 cloves Salt : to taste Pepper : 1 tsp Chili flakes : 1 tsp Rosemary : 1/2 Tsp Oregano : 1/2 Tsp For glaze Ketchup : 2 Tbs Coconut sugar : 1 Tbs Apple cider vinegar :1 Tbs Soya sauce : 1 Tbs Instructions: Preheat oven at 180C. Cook lentil according to instructions on packet. Prepare vegetables. In a pan heat oil add garlic and onion, Fry until color turns to golden brown. Add chopped bell peppers and grated carrots. Stir fry until veggies softened. Now add Raisins, breadcrumbs, oats , Walnuts and seasoning. Continue cooking for 5 minutes. Blend cooked lentils. Prepare flax seed egg by adding water into grounded flax seeds. Add blended lentils and flax seed egg into cooked vegetable mixture. Mix well and set this mixture gently and firmly into loaf pan. Bake for 35 o 40 Minutes on 180C or until its corner turns brown. Once baked transfer from loaf pan to board and coat with glaze. Once cool down, carefully slice the loaf into slabs. Serve immediately. xoxo Get Set Healthy

WRITING.TEXT: RECIPES: ----- ROASTED BELL PEPPER SPINACH PASTA ----- SERVE : 2 INGREDIENTS Whole wheat fettuccine Pasta : 4 oz FOR CREAMY PASTA SAUCE: Bell Peppers: 2 Medium Spinach Leaves : 1/2 cup Chickpeas : 1/2 cup Green Chilies : 2 Oil: 1/2 Tsp Garlic : 1 Tsp Salt: 1 Tsp Crushed Red chili flakes: 1/2 Tsp Coriander Powder : 1/2 Tsp Oregano: 1/4 Tsp FOR GARNISH: Cherry tomatoes : 1/2 cup Olives: 1/4 cup Slice Bell Pepper and toss in pinch of salt.Heat oven to 350 degrees F and roast red peppers on a baking tray about 15 - 20 minutes. Bring a large pot of water to a boil over high heat. Add the pasta and cook until tender (7-10) minutes. Drain the pasta in a colander. Transfer roasted peppers, spinach leaves , chick peas (Drained and washed) and green chilies. Blend until creamy and smooth. Once blended, set aside and heat a pan over medium heat and fry crushed garlic for a minute. Now add blended sauce to pan and cook for about 3 to 4 minutes. Add seasoning , salt, chili flakes, ground coriander powder and oregano. Taste and adjust seasonings as needed, adding more salt and pepper or nutritional yeast for flavor.Flavor should be very strong since the noodles don't have much flavor - so be generous with your seasonings. Now add some water as it will get thick and will stick to pan. Once it reaches a simmer, reduce heat to low and continue simmering. Once sauce is thickened to desired consistency add Pasta. Toss and cook for a minute or two . Garnish with cherry Tomatoes and Pitted Black Olives. ----- MUSHROOM SPINACH WRAP ----- For this wrap I am making whole wheat roti wrap. But you can use any store bought. If you want to learn its recipe do let me know in your comments below and I will make a video on it:) SERVE : 1 INGREDIENTS Whole wheat wrap ( or any other you like) : 1 Oil: 1 Tsp Onion chopped: 2 Tbl Button Mushrooms : 4/5 pcs Salt : To Taste Black Pepper: To Taste Baby Spinach Sliced Tomatoes Jalapeno For Sauce: Vegan Mayo : 2 Tsp Crushed Garlic: 1/2 Tsp Chili Flakes : 1/4 Tsp Dried Rosemary 1/4 Tsp Chop Onions and Slice Mushrooms. Heat Oil in a frying pan on medium heat and saute onions and Mushrooms, until they change color. Add Salt and Black pepper. Remove from heat and let them cool for a minute or two. Make sauce by mixing all ingredients. Spread baby spinach leaves, mushrooms mixture, sliced tomatoes , jalapenos and sauce over wheat tortilla and wrap it all up. Here you go with a creamy crunchy yummy lunch wrap which is also loved by meat lovers. ----- TADKA VEGETABLE OATS STEW ----- Serve: 2 Oil: 1/2 Tsp Onion: 1/2 Medium Minced Garlic: 1 Tsp Chopped Carrots: 1/4 cup Broccoli: 1 cup Green beans: 1/4 cup Sweet corn : 1/4 cup Peas: 1/4 cup Water: 3 cups Orange lentils soaked : 2 Tbl Salt: 1 Tsp Red Chili Powder: 1/4 Tsp Turmeric Powder: 1/4 Tsp Cumin Powder: 1/4 Tsp Garam Masala: 1/4 Tsp Black Cardamom : 1 Pcs Oats: 2 Tbl For Tadka Oil: 1 Tsp Fenugreek seeds : 1/4 Tsp Coriander Seeds: 1/4 Tsp Dried Red Chili : 3-4 Pcs Dried Rosemary : A Pinch Soak lentils for 3 to 4 hours. Prepare Vegetable. Heat oil in a pan and saute onions. Add minced garlic and fry on medium heat, don't burn your pan like me :) Add carrots, broccoli,green beans,sweet corn,and peas. You can add or skip vegetables according to your choice. Fry for a minute or two and then add for about 3 cups of water or in which your vegetable get soaked. Now add soaked lentil season them with salt, chili powder, turmeric powder, cumin powder, Garam Masala and black cardamom, and bring them to boil. cook them for 3 to 4 minutes , now add oats and cook for another 2 minutes. Remove from heat. For Tadka heat oil in a small frying pan and shallow fry fenugreek seeds, coriander seeds, dried red chili, and dried Rosemary. Dish out stew and pour tadrka oil on it. Serve hot with garlic bread and Enjoy:) Do let me know if you like or try these recipes . Love xoxoxo

Prepare your enchilada sauce. To make this enchilada sauce, Heat oil in a saucepan. Then whisk in the flour until combined, and cook for 1 minute or so. Then add Tomato paste and stir. Add some water or vegetable stock and keep stirring. Gradually whisk in your sauce until most of the clumps have dissolved and the sauce is smooth. Now add remaining water and bring it to boil. Add seasoning and let it simmer for 2 to 3 minutes and its ready to keep it aside.you can refrigerate this sauce for a week or so. For cheese sauce peel and cut potatoes in cubes and boil. Now in a blender add potatoes and some of their stock, seasoning and vegan butter. Blend into a smooth paste. In a large frying pan, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion and saut #233; for 2-3 minutes. Add sliced mushrooms and add seasoning. Once Mushrooms and onions are done add bell peppers and saute for 3 more minutes. stirring occasionally, when bell peppers get tender Remove pan from heat and set aside. To assemble the enchiladas, Spread enchilada sauce on the dish and for assembly Lay out a tortilla and spread two tablespoons of cheese sauce over the surface of the tortilla. Add a generous spoonful of the mushroom bell pepper mixture in a line down the center of the tortilla. Roll up tortilla and place in the enchilada dish. Assemble the remaining enchiladas. Then spread remaining enchilada and cheese sauce evenly over the top of the enchiladas. Video Recipe: [http://www.getsetvegan.com/vegan-holiday-breakfast-muffin/](http://www.getsetvegan.com/vegan-holiday-breakfast-muffin/) #8203; **\*\*Ingredients\*\*** **\*\*Dough\*\*** 1 cup Warm water 2 tsp Active dry yeast 1 tsp Sugar 2 cup Flour #8203; **\*\*Filling\*\*** 1/2 cup Soft sunflower butter 1/2 cup Raw sugar 1 tbs Cinnamon powder #8203; **\*\*Icing glaze\*\*** 1/2 cup Icing sugar 3 tbs Almond milk #8203; #8203; **\*\*Instructions\*\*** Preheat oven at 375F. So, it will be nice and warm when you put your muffins to bake. In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water. Make sure that your water is warm (not too cold, not too hot). Let it sit for 3 to 5 minutes. In a separate mixing bowl, combine the yeast mixture with 1 cup of flour and sugar. Add flour gradually and keep on mixing. At this stage, it will be kind of sticky. Stir in the rest of the flour. Mix it with your hands and form a ball shape. Cover and let the dough rise until doubled, about an hour or so, depending on the warmth of your kitchen. Once it is doubled in size, sprinkle some flour on a flat surface and knead the dough for 6-7 minutes, until it is smooth and elastic. Slice it in for equal parts. Next, roll the dough into a 1cm thickness flat round shape. In a bowl mix cinnamon and raw sugar. Spread soft sunflower butter on the surface of the dough and sprinkle a generous amount of sugar and cinnamon mixture. Roll into a cylindrical tube (see the video) and cut it into 1-inch pieces. Each cylindrical tube will yield around 12 pieces. Flat these cubes with your hands into a round shape while creating a marbling effect. You can also use a rolling pin, but I would recommend using your hands. It will be less messy and make a better marbling effect. Take 4 flatten dough circles overlapping each other, roll into a rose shape.Put them into a greased muffin tray and let them rise again for another 30 minutes in a warm place. Bake in the preheated oven at 375 F for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown. Remove from the oven and transfer to a wire rack. Allow cooling. Meanwhile, prepare your glaze by simply mixing icing sugar and almond milk. Add 1 tbs of milk at a time and whisk. Repeat until getting the desired consistency. Keep covered until ready to use, whisk again before drizzling on top of the cinnamon buns. Sprinkle some more cinnamon and sugar on top and serve.

While the jackfruit is cooking warm the taco shells according to their package directions. Slice avocado, onions, cabbage and tomatoes. Recipe Ingredients Pumpkin Puree: 1/3 cup Coconut Oil: 1/4 cup (melted and cooled) Brown Sugar: 1/2 cup Almond Flour: 11/2 cup Baking Powder: 1/2 tsp Cinnamon Powder: 1/4 tsp Ginger Powder: 1/4Tsp #8203; Instructions: Preheat oven to 350F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and set aside. #8203; In a large bowl, add the pumpkin puree, coconut oil, and brown sugar. Mix until well combined and smooth. Next add in almond flour, baking powder, cinnamon powder, and ginger powder. Mix until there are no lumps and form a nice thick paste-like texture. #8203; Cover the bowl and refrigerate it for 30 min.
